We timed this trip up strategically with the Red Moon because I know that gets the deer on their feet and especially the big mature bucks. Our first afternoon sit, we are in the game right off the bat and I am confident that with a little adjustment to our set up we will be right in the game. As patternable as he was during the early season, he gave Kyle the slip and went nocturnal. It wasn't until early November during the Red Moon on a perfect afternoon during the rut where Kyle was able to lay eyes on DKM for the first time. After seeing 14 bucks running wild, DKM finally showed himself and the rest is history. Here is the story of the infamous DKM.
